getRFC82xInternetAddress

public java.lang.String getRFC82xInternetAddress()
Gets the RFC821 or RFC822 internet address * A name that conforms to RFC 821 or RFC 822 is interpreted as an Internet address. Examples of Internet addresses are as follows:
  • jbg@us.acme.com
  • "John B Goode"
  • "John B Goode" (Sales) (East)

Returns:
the Internet address, comprised of the at least the minimum RFC821 Address. If no RFC821 Address exists a blank string is returned.
See Also:
getAddr821(), RFC822name.getAddr822Full()

getGroups

public java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> getGroups(java.lang.String serverName)
Description copied from interface: Name
Gets groups for the person / group / server etc the Name object pertains to.
The groups include the hierarchical name for the Name object, all Group entries that Name is a member of, and any OUs and O the name relates to.

Sample output: CN=admin/O=Intec-PW,admin,*,*\/O=Intec-PW,LocalDomainAdmins,Domino Developers,SEAS TestRole - Y1

Specified by:
getGroups in interface Name
Parameters:
serverName - String server name to check against
Returns:
Collection of any Domino Directory Person or Group the Name is found in, plus generic hierarchical responses
